#Text=Wikinews interviews Augustus Sol Invictus , Libertarian Party candidate for U.S. Senate
#Text=Monday , May 16 , 2016
#Text=Augustus Sol InvictusImage : Bryan Rapoza .
#Text=Augustus Sol Invictus

#Text=, an Orlando , Florida attorney currently seeking the Libertarian Party ' s nomination for the U.S. Senate seat being vacated by former Republican presidential candidate Marco Rubio , took part in a short interview with Wikinews reporter William S. Saturn to discuss his background , political views , and unorthodox campaign for the Senate .

#Text=Invictus , whose name was changed from his birth name to the Latin for " majestic unconquered sun " , has received media coverage for previously expressing fascistic views and participating in pagan rituals .

column1: #Text=While in law school , he penned an article advocating a eugenics program , and in 2013 , he wrote a " departure memo " renouncing his U.S. citizenship and law license while announcing plans to go into the wilderness until a civil war .

column1: #Text=He returned after making a pilgrimage from Orlando to the Mojave Desert , where he fasted for a week .

#Text=Upon his return to Florida , he sacrificed a goat and drank its blood . Former Libertarian Party of Florida chairman Adrian Wyllie resigned his chairmanship in protest of Invictus 's candidacy .
#Text=Though initially uncontested for the nomination , Invictus has recently received a challenge from information technology specialist Paul Stanton .
#Text=Political operative Roger Stone opened an exploratory committee to consider running for the nomination but has not shown further interest .
#Text=The primary election is to be held August 30 .
#Text=To qualify for the ballot , a candidate must either pay a US$ 10,000 fee or collect 100,000 signatures .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Background
#Text=( (
#Text=William S. Saturn
#Text=) )
#Text=Why did you change your name to Augustus Sol Invictus ?
#Text=Augustus Sol Invictus
#Text=: I was given my name in a religious initiation when I was twenty-one .
#Text=I usually analogize it to Roman Catholics taking a new name at Confirmation .
#Text=No one ever changes their name legally after such an initiation , as it is usually reserved for religious pursuits .
#Text=But I changed my name legally to my religious name so that my mundane and religious lives would be one .
#Text=( (
#Text=WSS
#Text=) )
#Text=What is your history with electoral politics ? Which political candidates have you previously supported or endorsed ?
#Text=Invictus
#Text=: I have no such history , and I have never made an endorsement .
#Text=I consider myself an outsider .
#Text=Truth be told , I consider myself a revolutionary more than a politician .
#Text=( (
#Text=WSS
#Text=) )
#Text=How do you feel about Republican front-runner Donald Trump and his campaign for president ?
#Text=Invictus

#Text=: Donald Trump is a cultural icon , and for that I love him . As for his presidential campaign , I am forced to remain neutral , as I cannot endorse anyone for President without it being thought that I have adopted their platform as my own .
#Text=Invictus says outgoing Senator Marco Rubio ( shown above ) , " is a horse-trader , a slimy smiler , the quintessential politician .
